name: I Dig Vinyl by Socialfabrik
description:
Vinyl isn't dead. It is not on life-support. And it certainly isn't going anywhere fast. In fact, it's popularity is back on the rise and that's thanks to the audiophiles, the wax enthusiasts & the record junkies keeping the medium alive.

With vinyl comes the fine art of crate digging, where record collectors, DJs & beat makers go searching for old, hard-to-find and unusual records, sometimes to sample, sometimes for use in new compositions and sometimes, just to play and appreciate.

With this design you can proudly show your love of the format and all it entails. Whether you are the type who just likes to play their dad's old 45's from time to time or someone with acres of dusty shelves like Jazzy Jeff or Pete Rock, this one is for you.


100% cotton.
Classic fit Earth Positive Jersey T-shirt.
White screenprint on navy.

name: Kubrick by Stan Chow
description:
This design is a tribute to maverick film director, Stanley Kubrick. He made just 13 feature films in a career that spanned more than 40 years, but this innovative visionary will be forever known as one of the most eccentric and reclusive directors of all time. His body of work includes such masterpieces as Spartacus, Lolita, Dr Strangelove, 2001: A Space Odyssey, A Clockwork Orange, The Shining and Full Metal Jacket.

This design is available exclusively to Socialfabrik, courtesy of Manchester based illustrator Stan Chow. 

Stan is one of the most highly respected and established artists in the UK right now, his portraits of the cast of Mad Men caused quite a storm in 2010 and his design for The White Stripes USB memory stick was nominated for a Grammy Award. His work can be seen regularly in the New Yorker.


100% cotton.
Classic fit white Jersey T-shirt.

name: Moondog by Ben Lamb
description:
This design is a tribute to the legendary Moondog, the eccentric blind composer, poet, musician & inventor of musical instruments who deliberately lived on the streets of NYC for 20 years. Thanks to his unconventional outfits, based on his own interpretation of the Norse god Odin, he was known for much of his life as "The Viking of 6th Avenue" 

His music has been covered by artists such as Janis Joplin, Prefab Sprout and Antony & The Johnsons to name a few. The track 'Stamping Ground' was featured in the film 'The Big Lebowski' and the track 'Bird's Lament' was remixed by Mr Scruff for his tune 'Get a Move on'.

This portrait has been designed exclusively for Socialfabrik by Ben Lamb, an illustrator and designer based in Manchester. Drawn in his highly detailed trademark style, Ben's illustration has a cosmic tone reminiscent of Jack Kirby's comic art for Silver Surfer, Fantastic Four & New Gods.

Ben's previous clients have included Levis Vintage, Jameson Irish Whiskey, Oi Polloi, Sperry Top-Sider, Piccadilly Records & Fader Magazine. You can find more of his excellent work at www.blamb.co.uk

100% cotton.
Classic fit Earth Positive Jersey T-shirt.
Moonlight grey screenprint on navy.

name: I Am The Music by Boris Pelcer
description:
Music is what thought, emotion & life sound like. Your every gesture, linguistic & physical interaction with all things is music in the making. As such you are the source of your own life's music & don't you forget it.

This design is available exclusively to Socialfabrik, courtesy of U.S based designer Boris Pelcer.

Originally from Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Boris Pelcer is a Graphic Designer, Illustrator, Letterer & Typographer now working in the U.S. His Typographic & Lettering work has caught the attention of many all across the globe and he has worked for Urban Outfitters, Spencer's, Zumiez, Hot Topic, Harley Davidson, Miller Brewing Co., Target & Kohl's. He has also been awarded by the Society of Illustrators & had work published in publications such as CMYK Magazine. Boris' typographic titles can currently be seen in the opening sequence for 'Davinci's Demons' on the Starz network.




100% cotton.
Classic fit Jersey T-shirt.
White screenprint on navy.

name: Nerd Army by Hammo
description:
It’s geek versus the world. But this guy’s got help. From high up in the clouds, this nerd is out to exact his vengeance, backed by an army of remote-control robots to do his bidding, this little guy doesn’t seem so little anymore...

Designed exclusively for Socialfabrik by Hammo AKA Nick Hamilton, an illustrator and graffiti artist based in Manchester.

Working across a range of media including digital illustrations, painted canvasses & murals, and influenced by a childhood filled with superheroes and comic books – Hammo’s distinctive pieces are recognisable by their bold lines and razor sharp attention to detail. His characteristic style and themes can be seen all over Manchester & beyond, and in the work he has produced for clients such as Playstation, K-Swiss and Diesel.

100% cotton.
Classic fit Jersey T-shirt.
Black & White screenprint on light blue.

description:

name: The Thug (Grey) by Socialfabrik
description:
The police forms call him Advanced Silhouette SP-83A; in some gun shops, he is B-60. He is widely known in police and gun-club circles as 'The Thug', a life-size, two-dimensional target that every New York City police officer has shot at since the early 1960's. 

Officially retired by the NYPD, he walks the streets amongst us, emblazoned on this iconic design.

Now, anybody can be a target.

100% cotton.
Classic fit Jersey T-shirt.
Black screenprint on grey
